                <td bgcolor="#37437B" valign="top"><font color="white" face="verdana" size="2"><small>Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;01/26/2004&nbsp;: 09:48:18 AM</small><hr size="1"><span class="spnMessageText"> I hear that tribute allows you to turn in droppable gear or platinum.  This gives you a tribute balance, in Beta 1pp=1 Tribute point.  <br /><br />You can then choose up to 5 tribute rewards.  The rewards are regen, FT, +stat, and focus effects.  <br /><br />You're told how much your tribute reward will cost, and that cost is deducted from your balance over time.  For instance, elect to get FT5 with a tribute balance of 400 gives you FT5 for about 4 hours.  Different types of rewards seem to be deducted differently.<br /><br />Tribute costs will likely change when this goes live.  An interesting PP synch.</span></font></td>
